  "prompt": "Do clairvoyant readings work?",
  "response": "The effectiveness of clairvoyant readings is a matter of personal belief and skepticism. Some individuals find value, guidance, and comfort in these readings, feeling that they provide insights or affirmations. However, scientific evidence does not support the existence of clairvoyant abilities. Skeptics argue that readings rely on cold reading techniques, psychological manipulation, and the willingness of the client to believe in them.\n\nUltimately, the perception of whether clairvoyant readings work depends on individual experiences, beliefs, and their approach to the information provided during the readings.",
